N
N \equiv a \pmod{m}
N \equiv b \pmod{n}
\quad\ \ N \,\equiv\, b + \beta\, n \,\equiv\, b + n\ \left[ \dfrac{(a-b)}n\ {\rm mod}\ m\right]\!\!\pmod{mn}
n, m
(n, m) = 1
x, y
N\equiv a\pmod{m}
N\equiv b\pmod{n}
 \begin{align} 1 &= mx+ny &\text{so}\\ a-b &=mx(a-b)+ny(a-b)\\  &=m[x(a-b)]+n[y(a-b)]\\  &= m\alpha+n\beta \end{align} 
 a-\alpha m =N= b+\beta n 
